Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce}, if necessary. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Finely chop @parsley{¼%ounce}.

Combine @garlic powder{¼%tsp} and @chili powder{¼%tsp} in a #small bowl{}. (You'll use the rest of the @garlic powder{1%tsp} and @chili powder{1%tsp} later.)

Toss green beans, bell pepper, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1.5%tablespoon}, remaining garlic powder, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add parsley, minced onion, @olive oil{1.5%tablespoon}, and @red wine vinegar{1%tsp} to bowl with reserved garlic powder and chili powder. Stir to combine; season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a little more vinegar if you prefer a tangier chimichurri.

Halve @ciabatta bread{1} lengthwise and spread with half the garlic herb butter. Place on a second baking sheet and top with @Italian cheese blend{½%cup}. Set aside (you'll finish the cheesy bread in Step 6).

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with remaining chili powder, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Remove pan from heat. Add remaining garlic herb butter to pan; spoon melted butter over steak until coated. Transfer steak to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

When veggies are done, remove from oven.

Transfer baking sheet with cheesy bread to top rack; broil until cheese is golden and bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to make sure it doesn't burn!

Slice cheesy bread on a diagonal into triangles. Slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, veggies, and cheesy bread between plates. Spoon half the chimichurri over steak. Serve with remaining chimichurri on the side for dipping.